# Free Hosting Deployment Plan — ChatDB

## Goal

Deploy ChatDB (FastAPI backend + React/Vite frontend) to **production on the internet for $0/month** using free-tier cloud services.

## Previous Work

Docker deployment was set up locally (Dockerfiles for both services + `docker-compose.yml`), but that only works for local containers — it doesn't make the app accessible on the internet. We need actual cloud hosting.

---

## Hosting Strategy

| Service | Platform | Cost | URL Pattern |
|---------|----------|------|-------------|
| **Backend** (FastAPI + Python) | **Render** | Free tier | `https://chatdb-api.onrender.com` |
| **Frontend** (React/Vite) | **Vercel** | Free tier | `https://chatdb.vercel.app` |

### Why This Combo?

- **Render Free Tier**: Supports Docker containers, persistent disk (for SQLite files), auto-deploy from GitHub, free SSL. No credit card required.
- **Vercel Free Tier**: Purpose-built for React/Vite apps, instant global CDN, auto-deploy from GitHub, free SSL. No credit card required.
- Both platforms have generous upgrade paths when your user base grows.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Render free tier limitation**: The backend will "spin down" after 15 minutes of inactivity, causing a ~30-50 second cold start on the first request. This is normal for free tier — users will see a brief loading delay after the app has been idle.

> [!WARNING]
> **Render free tier disk**: Render free tier does NOT include persistent disk. SQLite databases and uploaded files will reset on every deploy/restart. This is acceptable for a demo/early launch. When you grow, you can upgrade to a paid instance ($7/month) to get persistent storage, or migrate to a PostgreSQL database (Render offers a free PostgreSQL instance too but it expires after 90 days).

