## Deployment Steps (I'll execute these)

### Step 1: Prepare Files
1. Create root `.gitignore`
2. Create `render.yaml`
3. Create `frontend/vercel.json`
4. Update backend Dockerfile to use `$PORT`
5. Update `.env.example`

### Step 2: Initialize Git & Push to GitHub
1. `git init` in project root
2. Create `.gitignore`
3. `git add .` → `git commit`
4. Create GitHub repo & push

### Step 3: Deploy Backend to Render
1. Go to [render.com](https://render.com) → Sign up with GitHub
2. New Web Service → Connect repo → Select `backend` as root directory
3. Set environment variables (GROQ_API_KEY, FRONTEND_URL)
4. Deploy → Get URL (e.g., `https://chatdb-api.onrender.com`)

### Step 4: Deploy Frontend to Vercel
1. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → Sign up with GitHub
2. Import repo → Set `frontend` as root directory
3. Set env var: `VITE_API_URL=https://chatdb-api.onrender.com/api`
4. Deploy → Get URL (e.g., `https://chatdb.vercel.app`)

### Step 5: Update Backend CORS
1. Update `FRONTEND_URL` env var on Render to include the Vercel domain

